1
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:16,599
Mom, George is missing from her room.

2
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:18,143
I already searched the whole house

3
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:19,769
- but she's nowhere to be found.
- What?

4
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:21,980
<i>Where did she go?</i>

5
00:00:22,063 --> 00:00:23,940
George? George.

6
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:26,985
PREVIOUSLY

7
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:29,654
George, are you okay?

8
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:31,114
George, talk to us.

9
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:32,365
Talk to me.

10
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:33,783
Come here, my dear.

11
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,577
What did you do to George?

12
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,078
- Sir Galvan, don't. Please.
- Don't.

13
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:37,996
- Sir Galvan, don't.
- Don't.

14
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:39,581
She killed my grandson

15
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:41,708
and now she is trying to hurt George.

16
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:42,917
Sam saved her.

17
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:44,377
Ask Ando.

18
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:45,378
That's true, sir.

19
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:48,131
<i>Next time Barbara comes here,</i>

20
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,883
<i>inform me right away.</i>

21
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:50,800
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

22
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,886
<i>You're so shameless, right?</i>

23
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:57,599
You try to comfort George
after you killed her baby?

24
00:00:57,682 --> 00:00:58,641
Grief faker.

25
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:01,061
Such a wolf in sheep's clothing.

26
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,687
Hey, you're really getting on my nerves.

27
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,606
And I don't want to see your face

28
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:06,399
because you are cheap.

29
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:07,942
Well, then close your eyes.

30
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,444
You are rude.

31
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,905
That's for what you did to my mother.

32
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:16,576
Don't try to use your bitchy ways on me

33
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:18,495
because if you're a witch, I'm worse.

34
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:21,664
If you're a monster, I can be one too.

35
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:24,667
<i>Be thankful I can still be human.</i>

36
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:28,213
Forgive me because I failed
to protect you.

37
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:31,382
<i>You will see your daddy in heaven.</i>

38
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:34,177
<i>Hug him for me, okay?</i>

39
00:01:35,136 --> 00:01:36,304
<i>I love you so much.</i>

40
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:43,394
Thank you.

41
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,735
My condolences, Galvan.

42
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:52,278
Thank you, Aurora.

43
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,656
George…

44
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,372
Galvan…

45
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:06,209
Did you know
that Samantha wants to come here?

46
00:02:23,893 --> 00:02:24,727
There they are.

47
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,365
What are you doing here?

48
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:23,369
The killer has no right to sympathize

49
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:24,871
with the person she killed.

50
00:03:24,954 --> 00:03:25,997
Get out of here, Sam.

51
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,749
Auntie Ruth, I'm begging you.

52
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:29,834
Even if we just stay here.

53
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:30,877
We'll just stay here.

54
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,836
Sam!

55
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:34,505
Can't you understand?

56
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:36,758
Don't you ever go near George.

57
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:38,927
I don't want her to see your face.

58
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:42,138
You will only see each other in court.

59
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,681
That's enough.

60
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:46,517
I don't want any fighting,.

61
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:47,602
I don't want trouble.

62
00:03:47,685 --> 00:03:49,354
I don't want to sue anymore.

63
00:03:49,437 --> 00:03:51,564
What? No, George.

64
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:54,317
I won't allow that woman
not to be held accountable.

65
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:58,571
If you don't want to,
I will pursue the case.

66
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:00,573
And then what?

67
00:04:01,157 --> 00:04:03,743
Will that bring back my baby?

68
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:05,870
Let's finish this memorial.

69
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,247
It's embarrassing to Father.

70
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,457
- But…
- Dad, please.

71
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:12,043
I've already made up my mind.

72
00:04:12,126 --> 00:04:13,127
My mind is a mess,

73
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:14,837
I don't want to add to it.

74
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:20,969
I just want to be able
to mourn my baby's death properly.

75
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:24,347
Fine.

76
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:27,308
But, we're not done talking yet.

77
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:31,562
And you, leave!

78
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:46,995
George…

79
00:04:55,461 --> 00:04:58,256
Sam, it looks like George
will finally forgive you.

80
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,175
Don't cry anymore.

81
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:05,096
Ma'am Sam, someone wants you to have this.

82
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:37,128
DIG DEEPER, I THINK AURORA
AND YOUR FATHER HAD A CHILD.

83
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:44,343
Did you see who left this?

84
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:47,346
A driver handed it over
at the main gate. I didn't see it.

85
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:51,392
Sam, where are you going?

86
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:55,188
Did you see who left this?

87
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,523
Did you see the license number?
What type of car?

88
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:58,983
No, ma'am.

89
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,486
A driver handed it over at the main gate.

90
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:03,571
You did not take note of it?

91
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:07,116
He just handed the letter
and the flower to me,

92
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,243
and then he left in a hurry.

93
00:06:09,327 --> 00:06:10,995
Let's just check the CCTV,

94
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:13,289
so we can find out the license number.

95
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:47,198
So, what's the latest with Leonor?

96
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:52,370
Do you know that she has a new boyfriend?

97
00:06:52,453 --> 00:06:53,788
A drug lord.

98
00:06:53,871 --> 00:06:55,832
- No way.
- Yes…

99
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:15,685
Ma'am, here it is.
It has been forwarded to me.

100
00:07:16,352 --> 00:07:17,812
Play it.

101
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:24,694
Ma'am, that's the car
that left the flower.

102
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:27,238
Can you see the license number?

103
00:07:27,321 --> 00:07:29,073
- Can we zoom in?
- Yes.

104
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:32,326
Wait, I'll take a picture.

105
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,369
Here it is.

106
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:42,920
The reunion for our sorority
is coming up soon.

107
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,839
I have to book a flight to Singapore,

108
00:07:44,922 --> 00:07:46,632
so I can talk to my designer.

109
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:47,842
Are you going?

110
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:50,052
To the sorority reunion?

111
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:52,930
- Yes.
- Darling, Barry.

112
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:56,350
I was, still am, and will always be

113
00:07:56,434 --> 00:08:01,522
the best NPU Lambda Epsilon Alpha

114
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:04,233
sorority grand sister.

115
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:06,652
My presence is always anticipated,

116
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:08,279
and you know that.

117
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:12,617
Did I ever miss our annual reunion?

118
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:14,702
Yes.

119
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:15,953
Sam…

120
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,456
I've been searching
for you for some time now.

121
00:08:18,539 --> 00:08:19,874
What's happening?

122
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:23,461
Mother, remember the woman
who went to Francis' wake,

123
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:24,545
the one with the letter?

124
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:27,590
Yes, about the gas mask
in Aurora's basement.

125
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:29,717
She left a clue again.

126
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:31,427
What clue?

127
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:34,055
It's about Dad.

128
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:37,058
I think it was…

129
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:40,102
I think 1994.

130
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:44,023
You were gone for a year.

131
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:47,777
You know, I think some people
think that you died.

132
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:48,861
Gosh, Auro.

133
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:50,488
I got so worried about you.

134
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:57,286
I went to Europe that year
for a sabbatical year.

135
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,121
Yeah, I remember.

136
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:02,917
But, I also remember when you got back,

137
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,877
you gained a lot of weight.

138
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:06,379
You looked like you had gaven birth.

139
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:09,757
There is something I need
to know about Dad.

140
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,051
I'll probably wait for the next letter.

141
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,931
Thank you. Let's go, Mother.

142
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:18,266
All right, ma'am.

143
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,772
Auro, please be honest with me.

144
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,484
What really happened to you in Europe?

145
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:31,195
Why were you gone for a year,

146
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,531
and when you got back here

147
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:35,908
you were so fat?

148
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:37,285
What happened?

149
00:09:38,703 --> 00:09:40,830
Shut up, Barry.

150
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:43,165
Respect the dead.

151
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:45,167
Stop gossiping around.

152
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,294
God.

153
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:24,790
George, about what you told me earlier,

154
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,000
tell me it was a joke.

155
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:29,420
That was true, Dad.

156
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,589
I don't want to sue Sam anymore.

157
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:35,134
What did your contact say
in the transportation office?

158
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,136
They are overloaded right now.

159
00:10:37,219 --> 00:10:39,013
They have heaps of work.

160
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,806
Whose license number was that?

161
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,267
The woman who went to the wake.

162
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:44,518
Do you remember that?

163
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:47,563
Sam, who was that?

164
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,106
I don't know,

165
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:51,108
but she's been looking at me
for some time now.

166
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,693
It seems she left something.

167
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:56,906
Why didn't you tell me right away?

168
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,665
Hello? Hello, Buddy.

169
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:08,084
Can you prioritize my request?

170
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,502
I really need the info.

171
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,962
Are you serious?

172
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:17,051
You won't avenge your baby?

173
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:18,552
What's happening to you?

174
00:11:19,887 --> 00:11:22,473
I just had a realization, Dad.

175
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:25,184
What Sofia said struck me.

176
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:27,603
I will just accept what happened

177
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:29,021
because I don't want…

178
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:31,899
I don't want to remember
the loss of my son

179
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:33,984
over and over again.

180
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,986
No, George.

181
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:39,615
If you won't push through with the case,

182
00:11:39,698 --> 00:11:41,450
then I will do it.

183
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:43,160
No, Dad.

184
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:46,080
I will not cooperate.

185
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:50,334
I also attacked Sam. You and Mom too.

186
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,002
We all attacked her.

187
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:56,257
If I sue her, she'll just sue me back.

188
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:57,967
There will be a never-ending lawsuit.

189
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,635
I don't want it anymore.

190
00:12:08,727 --> 00:12:10,521
Talk to your daughter.

191
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:24,076
Why did you ask for my help
and not Sergeant Royales?

192
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:28,956
Because this is about Mom Aurora and Dad.

193
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:31,500
And one more thing, Sergeant Royales

194
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,128
is already doing a lot of things.
I don't want to add to it.

195
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:38,090
And…

196
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:40,384
I'm just following the information.

197
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:42,803
I don't know if it's really legit.

198
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:47,600
Or if the mastermind
of the Palacios killer

199
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:51,187
is just using this
to divert you from the truth.

200
00:12:58,194 --> 00:12:59,695
George…

201
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,407
What's happening?

202
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:13,375
I made you all believe, right?

203
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:17,546
So, I guess I made Sam believe

204
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,256
that I'll be able to forgive her.

205
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:25,137
But, the last clue that she gave

206
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,598
took us to the gas mask.

207
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:30,184
And now it's about Dad.

208
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:34,188
That woman knows a lot of things.

209
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:42,071
Here, my friend has already replied.

210
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:44,532
- I'll forward it to you.
- Okay.

211
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:46,951
Mom…

212
00:13:47,034 --> 00:13:49,745
my anger towards Sam will never disappear

213
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:51,914
until I die.

214
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,795
Wait, George.

215
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,297
So, you're just fooling Sam?

216
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,216
You're playing with her?

217
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:06,929
You're making her believe
that you have forgiven her,

218
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,347
but you'll still
push through with the lawsuit?

219
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:13,435
There.

220
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:18,357
Boris Tayuman, lawyer.

221
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,193
A man?

222
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:25,030
Maybe that's her husband or son.

223
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:29,702
I will find out once I see that woman.

224
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:35,541
George, I really can't understand.

225
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:39,503
I will no longer sue Sam.

226
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:42,548
I will patch things up with her.

227
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:46,760
I will make her believe that we're okay.

228
00:14:46,844 --> 00:14:48,387
I will win her over

229
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,849
and once I get her trust,

230
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:54,643
it will be easier for me to get her baby

231
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,020
once she gives birth.

232
00:14:56,937 --> 00:15:00,024
Um, about…

233
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,567
you and Ma'am George…

234
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:06,155
Earlier I saw you call her

235
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:08,407
and she nodded.

236
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:11,410
It seems she is no longer mad.

237
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,705
I think, Ma'am Sam,

238
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,416
just a little push and she'll forgive you.

239
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,295
I hope so.

240
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:26,467
I'm thinking of Hong Kong…

241
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:30,596
No, Europe.

242
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:36,310
That's where I'll take
and raise Sam's baby…

243
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:39,104
My future child.

244
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:54,495
Come in.

245
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:03,003
Hi.

246
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:05,714
Mommy, how are you feeling?

247
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:08,008
I brought you your meds.

248
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:11,845
You're so sweet, Sofia.

249
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,180
Thank you.

250
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:16,850
Yeah, but I'm feeling better.

251
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:22,064
I think I heard…

252
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:26,819
your daddy shouting outside.

253
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:30,656
- Why?
- Dad is mad at George right now.

254
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,324
Thank you.

255
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:36,245
Ivan.

256
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:38,288
What's the update

257
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:39,748
on the car rental services
I asked you to check?

258
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:41,583
Yes, the team made progress.

259
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,712
On the list of the Palacios

260
00:16:44,795 --> 00:16:46,130
that we checked,

261
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:47,965
there's one name that made a hit.

262
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:49,299
It's Ms. Trano.

263
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,719
Anyway, Mom. Take your meds, okay?

264
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:53,178
You've already eaten, right?

265
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,389
Yeah, I've already eaten.

266
00:16:56,473 --> 00:16:57,433
Don't worry.

267
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,018
I'll drink my meds, okay?

268
00:16:59,101 --> 00:17:01,103
- Okay.
- Thank you, Sofia.

269
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:29,506
There you are.

270
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:38,599
Miss Trano?

271
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,311
It's Vivian? Sir Galvan's girlfriend?

272
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:46,231
Yes, we've already checked
her driver's license

273
